Class LFGraph

All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, DirectedGraph<LFVertex,LFEdge>, Graph<LFVertex,LFEdge>
public class LFGraph
extends DirectedMultigraph<LFVertex,LFEdge>

A graph representation of an LF. By default, LF graphs are empty. But populated LF graphs can be easily created using the LFGraphFactory class.

This class extends the DirectedMultigraph class from the org.jgrapht.graph package that provides some specialized methods for dealing with OpenCCG LFs. It provides some flexibility for edge creation by allowing an LFEdgeFactory to be specified at creation. The original LF structure is also reflected in the getLFAncestry(LFVertex), highestLFAncestors(), and highestLFAncestorOf(LFVertex) methods.

As a convenience, the method findVertexByNominal(Nominal) provides access to the vertex corresponding to a given nominal. This is implemented by a hash map so that the lookup takes place in constant time.

Author:
Scott Martin
See Also:

findVertexByNominal

public LFVertex findVertexByNominal(Nominal nominal)
Finds a vertex by its nominal. This method does a lookup on a dictionary mapping each vertex's nominal to members of theAbstractBaseGraph.vertexSet().

Parameters:
nominal - The nominal to test for.
Returns:
A vertex whose nominal is equivalent to the one specified, or null if none is present.
